paragraphs.title: What is the Schema?  How many records?
What is the average distance and average payment by car/vehicle
paragraphs.text:
%sql

SELECT vehicle_id, 
    mean(trip_distance) as avg_distance, 
    mean(payment_amount) as avg_payment, 
    mean(tip_amount) as avg_tip
    FROM rawdata_sql 
    GROUP BY vehicle_id 
    ORDER BY ${OrderBy=avg_distance,avg_distance|avg_payment|avg_tip} DESC 
    LIMIT 10

paragraphs.title: Model Prep
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

label_var    = "trip_distance"
feature_vars = ["passenger_count", "tolls_amount", "tip_amount", "pickup_day", "pickup_hour"]

# Generate Features Vector and Label
va = VectorAssembler(inputCols=feature_vars, outputCol="features")

# Added code to drop nulls / NAs
#modelprep1.count()
#modelprep1 = modelprep1.na.drop()
#modelprep1.count()

modeldata1 = va.transform(transformed1).withColumn("label", col(label_var))

training, testing = modeldata1.randomSplit([0.8, 0.2])

print "Training Data Count: " + str(training.count())
print "Testing Data Count:  " + str(testing.count())

result.msg:
Training Data Count: 562669

paragraphs.title: Modeling (Gradient Boosting Model)
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

gbt = GBTRegressor(featuresCol="features", labelCol="label", predictionCol="prediction", maxDepth=5, maxBins=32, maxIter=20, seed=12345)
gbtmodel = gbt.fit(training)

# Make predictions.
predictions = gbtmodel.transform(testing)

# Select example rows to display.
predictions.select("prediction", "label").show(20)

predictions.createOrReplaceTempView("predictions_sql")

paragraphs.title: Model Prediction Results (Label vs Prediction)
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select label, prediction from predictions_sql limit 1000
